Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
write_ilm_eco_db(25.10)                                write_ilm_eco_db(25.10)

Name
       write_ilm_eco_db

Syntax
       write_ilm_eco_db

       [-help]

       -cell <tcl_obj>]

       {-dir <directoryName>  | -module_model_tag <tagName>}

       Saves netlist and placement information changes::

              * Generates  a binary ECO file that can be read/loaded back to a
                block-level design

              * Generates  the  ECO  TCL  script  with  read_ilm_eco_db  -mod-
                ule_model_tag for iHDB

              * Output as corresponding ECO report file for viewing purpose

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description of the write_ilm_eco_db command. For
              a detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man write_ilm_eco_db

       -cell <tcl_obj>
              Specifies  a cell name for ECO information to be written out. If
              the specified cell name does not have any ECO change,  both  ECO
              and report files will be empty. If this option is not specified,
              the command will write ECO information for all ILMs specified in
              the design EVEN an ILM cell is not allowed for ECO. This to make
              sure  accumulated  ECO information will be preserved/saved as an
              ILM can be opened and then closed  later  during  the  flow.  If
              there  is  no  ECO change done to a particular cell, its ECO and
              report files will be empty.

       -dir <directoryName>
              Specifies a directory name where ECO files will  be  saved.  All
              the ECO and/or report files should be saved under the convention
              <dirName>/<cellName>/<cellName.eco>     and     <dirName>/<cell-
              Name>/<cellName.rpt>, respectively.

       -module_model_tag <tagName>
              Specifies the model tag name where ECO file, ECO  TCL,  and  its
              report  will be saved. This option should be used for Stylus hi-
              erarchical DB.

Related Information
              * read_ilm_eco_db

